\addvspace {10\p@ }
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2.1}{\ignorespaces Conceptual overview of the Medallion Lakehouse architecture in UrbanPulse.}}{5}{}%
\addvspace {10\p@ }
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.1}{\ignorespaces Use case diagram for the UrbanPulse platform.}}{9}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.2}{\ignorespaces High-level system architecture of UrbanPulse.}}{10}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.3}{\ignorespaces Dual-consumer data flow from Redpanda to Lakehouse and Online Feature Store.}}{13}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.4}{\ignorespaces Per-route Z-score over a 24-hour observation window (Grafana). Each line represents one directed inter-zone route. Spikes above the dashed threshold $\theta _r$ trigger the Z-score anomaly signal.}}{16}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.5}{\ignorespaces Optuna hyperparameter tuning validation across 20 routes. \textit {Left}: tuned vs.\ default anomaly score gap per route (all points above the diagonal indicate improvement). \textit {Right}: distribution of score gap delta (\texttt {tuned} $-$ \texttt {default}); all 20 routes show strictly positive improvement (mean $+0.023$, max $+0.047$).}}{18}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3.6}{\ignorespaces MLflow experiment view showing per-route \texttt {IsolationForest} training runs for the \texttt {traffic-anomaly-detection} experiment. Each row corresponds to one directed inter-zone route model.}}{18}{}%
\addvspace {10\p@ }
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.1}{\ignorespaces UrbanPulse complete system architecture: data ingestion from VietMap and Open-Meteo via Redpanda, medallion lakehouse (Bronze/Silver/Gold) on MinIO with Iceberg and Nessie, Online Service writing to PostgreSQL, Batch and ML Services tracked by MLflow, RAG pipeline via ChromaDB and Ollama, and Next.js frontend served through Traefik.}}{22}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.2}{\ignorespaces UrbanPulse service topology}}{24}{}%
\addvspace {10\p@ }
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.1}{\ignorespaces Redpanda Console: \texttt {traffic-route-bronze} topic with 67,428 messages (34.3~MiB) confirming continuous ingestion over the 54-day observation period.}}{28}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.2}{\ignorespaces Prefect flow schedules visualised as a Gantt-style timeline. Each row is one flow; bar width is proportional to schedule interval. Microbatch and Alerter fire every 5 minutes; Gold aggregation runs hourly; ML Retrain with RAG indexing runs every 6 hours.}}{29}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.3}{\ignorespaces Prefect 3.x Deployments view: seven active flows covering ingestion, batch promotion, model retraining, RAG indexing, and Telegram alerting.}}{30}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.4}{\ignorespaces AI Anomaly Explanation modal for the Zone~3~$\to $~Zone~4 route (Vietnamese output): Qwen2.5:3b structures its response into three sections --- \textit {Quan sát} (heavy\_ratio\,=\,4.1\%, zscore\,=\,$-1.53$, free-flowing), \textit {Nguyên nhân} (Friday 18:00 off-peak, industrial/port traffic decrease, stable weather at 26.5\textdegree C), and \textit {Đánh giá} (low-severity, positive free-flow event).}}{33}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.5}{\ignorespaces Urban Pulse AI Chat demonstrating bilingual capability: an English query ``how's the traffic now'' receives an English response reporting the Southern Port~$\to $~Western Periurban route at 10.9\% heavy ratio and overcast conditions at 29.5\textdegree C, retrieved from the PostgreSQL feature store and Open-Meteo feed via Qwen2.5:3b.}}{34}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.6}{\ignorespaces Traffic Metrics heatmap: tooltip showing a Z-score-only anomaly on the Coastal $\to $ Urban Core route at 08:00 ($Z = 4.22$), Apr 12--15, 2026.}}{35}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.7}{\ignorespaces Traffic Metrics heatmap: tooltip showing a dual-signal anomaly (\texttt {BOTH}) on the Coastal $\to $ Western route at 15:00 ($Z = 2.02$), Apr 12--15, 2026.}}{36}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.8}{\ignorespaces AI Heatmap Analysis panel (Vietnamese --- \textit {Phân tích Heatmap bằng AI}): Qwen2.5:3b identifies two dual-signal anomalies on Zone~3~$\to $~Zone~4 at 16:00 and 18:00, attributes them to logistics and industrial traffic, and lists Zone~1~$\to $~Zone~3/4 and Zone~2~$\to $~Zone~3/4 as single-signal developing congestion candidates.}}{36}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.9}{\ignorespaces AI Heatmap Analysis panel (English): the same four-part structure rendered in English confirms Zone~3~$\to $~Zone~4 dual-signal anomalies at 16:00 ($Z{=}3.4$) and 18:00 ($Z{=}2.5$), with root causes linked to the southern port industrial corridor and evening-shift logistics. Single-signal routes (Zone~1~$\to $~Zone~2, Zone~3~$\to $~Zone~5) are noted as isolated but significant events.}}{37}{}%
\addvspace {10\p@ }
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.1}{\ignorespaces Dremio EDA query on \texttt {nessie.gold.traffic\_hourly}: 20 routes, 76 days covered, confirming the Iceberg Gold table is correctly populated by the batch pipeline.}}{38}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.2}{\ignorespaces MLflow experiment \texttt {traffic-anomaly-detection}: 20 per-route runs all completed with status \textsc {finished} in $\sim $3.5~s each, confirming the ML Service retraining pipeline is stable.}}{40}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.3}{\ignorespaces MLflow per-route metric charts for \texttt {zone6 $\to $ zone5}: agreement = 0.96, Jaccard = 0.16, IForest rate = 0.01 (tuned contamination), 12 joint anomaly hours from 1,517 samples.}}{41}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.4}{\ignorespaces Model agreement (blue) and Jaccard similarity (orange) for five representative routes. Agreement consistently exceeds 0.90; Jaccard variation reflects route-specific traffic pattern stability.}}{42}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.5}{\ignorespaces Production Anomalies Per Hour (Apr 12--15, 2026): yellow = Z-Score only, green = IForest only, red = both detectors agree. Morning rush-hour clusters are visible, alongside a late-evening IForest-only spike near 23:00 on Apr~15.}}{43}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.6}{\ignorespaces Grafana Online Features dashboard (Apr 13--15, 2026): p50 = 153~ms, p95 = 318~ms, p99 = 336~ms ingestion-to-feature latency. Anomalous routes over time shown in the bottom-right panel.}}{44}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.7}{\ignorespaces Grafana Anomaly Detection dashboard (Apr 13--15, 2026): anomalous route count over time (top-left), maximum heavy-ratio Z-Score intensity reaching roughly 9 (top-right), and per-route Z-Score time series for all 20 routes (bottom-right).}}{44}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.8}{\ignorespaces Grafana Ingestion Service dashboard: periodic 5-minute burst pattern at 0.08--0.12 req/s confirming correct API polling cadence. Zero errors and zero warnings over the observed window.}}{45}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.9}{\ignorespaces Breakdown of \texttt {ingest\_lag\_ms}: the timestamp \texttt {ingest\_ts} is recorded by the Ingestion Service before the VietMap API call and embedded in the Kafka header; the Online Consumer stamps $t_{\text {now}}$ after the PostgreSQL UPSERT completes. All five stages run on the same host, keeping network overhead near zero.}}{45}{}%
\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.10}{\ignorespaces Grafana Urban Traffic Analytics dashboard: Bronze$\to $Silver 4,850 rows, Silver$\to $Gold 120 rows, Baseline 3,360 records. Batch job completion logs confirm error-free pipeline execution.}}{46}{}%
